// Requirements:
// - Add todos optimistically
// - Delete todos optimistically
// - If API call fails, rollback the change
// - Show success/error notifications
// - Handle network errors gracefully

flow.mentorSays:
Perfect! Here's the optimal solution approach:

```javascript
const [todos, setTodos] = useState([]);
const [error, setError] = useState(null);

const addTodo = async (text) => {
  const tempId = Date.now();
  const newTodo = { id: tempId, title: text, completed: false };

  // Optimistically add
  setTodos(prev => [...prev, newTodo]);

  try {
    const response = await fetch('/api/todos', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify({ title: text })
    });
    const savedTodo = await response.json();
    // Replace temp with real
    setTodos(prev => prev.map(t => t.id === tempId ? savedTodo : t));
  } catch (err) {
    // Rollback on error
    setTodos(prev => prev.filter(t => t.id !== tempId));
    setError('Failed to add todo');
  }
};
```

This solution demonstrates best practices for React development and shows how to properly implement Optimistic patterns, rollback.

